==English==
===Noun===
'''reference''' (''plural'': [[references]])

# a measurement one can compare to
# information about a person, provided by someone (a [[referee]]) with whom they are well acquainted

====Translations====
*Dutch: [[referentie]] ''f'', [[verwijzing]] ''f'', [[doorverwijzing]] ''f''
*{{fr}}: [[référence]] ''f''
*German: [[Referenz]] ''f''
*{{io}}: [[refero]]
*{{sv}}: [[referens]]

===Verb===
Despite what many are led to believe, "Reference" is not a verb. "Reference" is a noun. The correct form is "refer to". A few examples of other nouns that people commonly confuse with verbs are "vacation" and "Access". 

"Reference the dictionary for word meanings."
# Is incorrect and should be changed to:
"Refer to the dictionary for the meaning of words"
